st="text"
tar=tar.open("news20.tar.gz","r:gz")
t=codecs.open("n.txt","w+","utf-8")
for member in tar.getmembers():
    f=tar.extractfile(member)
    if f is not None:
        content = f.read()
        s=str(content, 'utf-8',errors='ignore')
        a=s.split('\n')
        s=''.join(a[35:])
        t.write(s)

Filter out Stem Words¶

In [31]:
p_stemmer = PorterStemmer()
In [32]:
texts = [p_stemmer.stem(i) for i in stopped_tokens]
In [53]:
stopwords = ['would', 'like', 'peopl', 'dont', 'time', 'also', 'know', 'use', 'think', 'make', 'even','could', 'said','system',
             'work','year','need','right','file','good','want','mani','well','thing','come','mean','look']
for word in list(texts):
    if word in stopwords:
       texts.remove(word)

Build a Dictionary - association word to numeric id¶

In [54]:
dictionary = corpora.Dictionary([texts])

Transform the collection of texts to a numerical form¶

In [55]:
corpus = [dictionary.doc2bow(text) for text in[texts]]
import pickle
pickle.dump(corpus, open('corpus.pkl', 'wb'))
dictionary.save('dictionary.gensim')

Using Scikit-Learn for Topic Modeling¶

vectorizer = CountVectorizer(min_df=5, max_df=0.9, 
                             stop_words='english', lowercase=True, 
                             token_pattern='[a-zA-Z\-][a-zA-Z\-]{2,}')
In [73]:
data_vectorized = vectorizer.fit_transform(texts)
In [74]:
def print_topics(model, vectorizer, top_n=10):
    for idx, topic in enumerate(model.components_):
        print("Topic %d:" % (idx))
        print([(vectorizer.get_feature_names()[i], topic[i])
                        for i in topic.argsort()[:-top_n - 1:-1]])

Plotting words and documents in 2D with SVD¶

In [81]:
svd = TruncatedSVD(n_components=2)
documents_2d = svd.fit_transform(data_vectorized)
 
df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['x', 'y', 'document'])
df['x'], df['y'], df['document'] = documents_2d[:,0], documents_2d[:,1], range(len(texts))
 
source = ColumnDataSource(ColumnDataSource.from_df(df))
labels = LabelSet(x="x", y="y", text="document", y_offset=8,
                  text_font_size="8pt", text_color="#555555",
                  source=source, text_align='center')
 
plot = figure(plot_width=600, plot_height=600)
plot.circle("x", "y", size=12, source=source, line_color="black", fill_alpha=0.8)
plot.add_layout(labels)
show(plot, notebook_handle=True)
